translated: Dalhammar, Carl Ingmar, engineer, Gothenburg, b. 30/11/03 in Lungsund, Värmland. Son of the first actuary, PhD B.A. Carlsson and Alma Svensson. Married to Gerda Bengtsson in 1931. Children: Kristina b. 1938, Margareta b. 1940, Lars b. 1943. He completed his secondary education at Östra Real in Stockholm in 1921 and graduated from the Royal Institute of Technology in 1926. He worked as a contractor at A-B Penta Works in Skövde from 1927-1929, then at Nydqvist & Holm AB diesel motor department in Trollhättan from 1929-1930, and as a contracting engineer at NOHAB Flygmotorfabr. AB from 1930-1935. He was the planner manager at Nydqvist & Holm AB from 1935-1939 and was the chief engineer at the Swedish Flygmotor AB in Trollhättan since 1939. He has been a member of the Swedish Engineering Association since 1926.
